assetProfile.longBusinessSummary: OLBA HEALTHCARE HOLDINGS, Inc. provides various solutions to medical institutions, research laboratories of universities and companies, nursing care facilities, and individuals in Japan. The company's medical equipment business engages in the wholesale of artificial joints, coronary stents, steel instruments, osteosynthesis materials made of metal and ceramics, ultrasonic scalpels, and pacemakers and catheters related to examination, diagnosis, and treatment of the heart and blood vessels; X-ray fluoroscopy and CT equipment for tumor and embolism treatment, and endoscopes for cancer treatment; and diagnostic imaging equipment, such as MRI and CT to ventilators, and intraoperative monitors, as well as operating room equipment, including shadowless lights. It also offers reagents and equipment for genetic research, cell culture, and protein analysis; automatic analyzers for biochemical, immunological, blood, etc.; and test reagents, as well as undertakes services for DNA analysis in the field of life sciences. The company's supply processing and distribution business provides goods management, information management, and purchase management services. Its nursing care products business engages in the sale and rental of nursing care equipment; sale of welfare equipment, such as portable toilets and bathing chairs; and home renovation works, as well as provision of nursing care services. The company was formerly known as Kawanishi Holdings, Inc. and changed its name to OLBA HEALTHCARE HOLDINGS, Inc. in January 2021. OLBA HEALTHCARE HOLDINGS, Inc. was founded in 1921 and is headquartered in Okayama, Japan.
